verses.text_plain: The elders which are among you I exhort, who am also an elder, and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and also a partaker of the glory that shall be revealed:
verses.verse_html: 1The elders which are among you I exhort, who am also an elder, and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and also a partaker of the glory that shall be revealed:

verses.text_plain: Feed the flock of God which is among you, taking the oversight thereof, not by constraint, but willingly; not for filthy lucre, but of a ready mind;
verses.verse_html: 2Feed the flock of God which is among you, taking the oversight thereof, not by constraint, but willingly; not for filthy lucre, but of a ready mind;

verses.text_plain: Neither as being lords over God’s heritage, but being ensamples to the flock.
verses.verse_html: 3Neither as being lords over God’s heritage, but being ensamples to the flock.

verses.text_plain: And when the chief Shepherd shall appear, ye shall receive a crown of glory that fadeth not away.
verses.verse_html: 4And when the chief Shepherd shall appear, ye shall receive a crown of glory that fadeth not away.

verses.text_plain: Likewise, ye younger, submit yourselves unto the elder. Yea, all of you be subject one to another, and be clothed with humility: for God resisteth the proud, and giveth grace to the humble.
verses.verse_html: 5Likewise, ye younger, submit yourselves unto the elder. Yea, all of you be subject one to another, and be clothed with humility: for God resisteth the proud, and giveth grace to the humble.

verses.text_plain: Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time:
verses.verse_html: 6Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time:

verses.text_plain: Casting all your care upon him; for he careth for you.
verses.verse_html: 7Casting all your care upon him; for he careth for you.

verses.text_plain: Be sober, be vigilant; because your adversary the devil, as a roaring lion, walketh about, seeking whom he may devour:
verses.verse_html: 8Be sober, be vigilant; because your adversary the devil, as a roaring lion, walketh about, seeking whom he may devour:

verses.text_plain: Whom resist stedfast in the faith, knowing that the same afflictions are accomplished in your brethren that are in the world.
verses.verse_html: 9Whom resist stedfast in the faith, knowing that the same afflictions are accomplished in your brethren that are in the world.

verses.text_plain: But the God of all grace, who hath called us unto his eternal glory by Christ Jesus, after that ye have suffered a while, make you perfect, stablish, strengthen, settle you.
verses.verse_html: 10But the God of all grace, who hath called us unto his eternal glory by Christ Jesus, after that ye have suffered a while, make you perfect, stablish, strengthen, settle you.

verses.text_plain: To him be glory and dominion for ever and ever. Amen.
verses.verse_html: 11To him be glory and dominion for ever and ever. Amen.

verses.text_plain: By Silvanus, a faithful brother unto you, as I suppose, I have written briefly, exhorting, and testifying that this is the true grace of God wherein ye stand.
verses.verse_html: 12By Silvanus, a faithful brother unto you, as I suppose, I have written briefly, exhorting, and testifying that this is the true grace of God wherein ye stand.

verses.text_plain: The church that is at Babylon, elected together with you, saluteth you; and so doth Marcus my son.
verses.verse_html: 13The church that is at Babylon, elected together with you, saluteth you; and so doth Marcus my son.

verses.text_plain: Greet ye one another with a kiss of charity. Peace be with you all that are in Christ Jesus. Amen.
verses.verse_html: 14Greet ye one another with a kiss of charity. Peace be with you all that are in Christ Jesus. Amen.
